    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/golden-halloumi-with-tzatziki-fruity-couscous-and-dessert/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle, then grate your\u00a0<strong>cucumber</strong></p><p>Separate your <strong>mint </strong>from your<strong> dill</strong>, and set aside the <strong>dill</strong> for later</p><p>Strip the\u00a0<strong>mint leaves</strong>\u00a0from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Cut your\u00a0<strong>lemon[s]</strong>\u00a0into wedges</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/golden-halloumi-with-tzatziki-fruity-couscous-and-dessert/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>vegetable stock mix\u00a0</strong>to a heatproof bowl with your\u00a0<strong>sultanas</strong>,\u00a0<strong>diced apricots</strong>\u00a0and\u00a0<strong>couscous</strong></p><p>Add 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span><strong>\u00a0boiled water</strong>, give everything a good mix up, cover and set aside for later \u2013 this is your<strong> fruity couscous</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/golden-halloumi-with-tzatziki-fruity-couscous-and-dessert/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your\u00a0<strong>natural yoghurt\u00a0</strong>to a bowl with the\u00a0<strong>grated cucumber </strong>and<strong> </strong>the <strong>chopped mint</strong></p><p>Add a drizzle of<strong>\u00a0olive oil\u00a0</strong>and the\u00a0juice\u00a0of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon wedges</strong>\u00a0and stir it all together \u2013 this is your\u00a0<strong>tzatziki</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/golden-halloumi-with-tzatziki-fruity-couscous-and-dessert/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong>\u00a0olive oil\u00a0</strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Cut your <strong>halloumi</strong> into 3 slices per person</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>halloumi</strong> <strong>slices</strong> and cook for 1-2 min on each side or until golden</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/golden-halloumi-with-tzatziki-fruity-couscous-and-dessert/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst\u00a0the halloumi is cooking, dice your <strong>tomato[es]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>dill</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/golden-halloumi-with-tzatziki-fruity-couscous-and-dessert/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>flaked almonds </strong>and <strong>diced tomato</strong> to the fruity couscous with a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and a big squeeze of <strong>lemon juice</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>and fluff everything up with a fork</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/golden-halloumi-with-tzatziki-fruity-couscous-and-dessert/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>golden</strong> <strong>halloumi </strong>with the <strong>tzatziki </strong>and <strong>fruity couscous</strong>\u00a0to the side</p><p>Garnish with the<strong> chopped dill </strong>and a<strong> lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
